================================================================
2) CLASS DIAGRAM
================================================================

2.1 Textual description

Inheritance:
- Staff extends User
- Admin extends User

Core domain classes:
- User, Profile, Address
- Category, Product, ProductVariant, InventoryLog
- Cart, CartItem
- Order, OrderItem, Payment
- Coupon, CouponRule
- WishlistItem
- Review, ReviewReply
- SupportTicket, ChatbotSession
- ReportSummary

Service classes:
- AuthService
- ProductService
- CartService
- OrderService
- PaymentService
- ReviewService
- CouponService
- SupportService
- ReportService

Main associations:
- User 1..1 Profile
- User 1..* Address
- Category 1..* Product
- Product 1..* ProductVariant
- ProductVariant 1..* InventoryLog
- User 1..1 Cart
- Cart 1..* CartItem
- User 1..* Order
- Order 1..* OrderItem
- Order 1..1 Payment
- User 1..* Review
- Product 1..* Review
- User 1..* WishlistItem
- User 1..* SupportTicket


2.2 PlantUML code (paste into PlantUML renderer)
//
@startuml
skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0

class User {
  +id: UUID
  +email: string
  +passwordHash: string
  +role: string
  +status: string
  +createdAt: datetime
}

class Staff
class Admin
User <|-- Staff
User <|-- Admin

class Profile {
  +userId: UUID
  +fullName: string
  +phone: string
  +avatarUrl: string
}

class Address {
  +id: UUID
  +userId: UUID
  +receiverName: string
  +phone: string
  +addressLine: string
  +isDefault: bool
}

class Category {
  +id: UUID
  +name: string
  +slug: string
}

class Product {
  +id: UUID
  +categoryId: UUID
  +name: string
  +price: decimal
  +status: string
}

class ProductVariant {
  +id: UUID
  +productId: UUID
  +color: string
  +size: string
  +stockQty: int
}

class InventoryLog {
  +id: UUID
  +variantId: UUID
  +changeQty: int
  +reason: string
  +createdAt: datetime
}

class Cart {
  +id: UUID
  +userId: UUID
}

class CartItem {
  +id: UUID
  +cartId: UUID
  +variantId: UUID
  +quantity: int
}

class Order {
  +id: UUID
  +userId: UUID
  +status: string
  +totalAmount: decimal
  +createdAt: datetime
}

class OrderItem {
  +id: UUID
  +orderId: UUID
  +variantId: UUID
  +quantity: int
  +unitPrice: decimal
}

class Payment {
  +id: UUID
  +orderId: UUID
  +method: string
  +status: string
  +paidAt: datetime
}

class Coupon {
  +id: UUID
  +code: string
  +discountType: string
  +discountValue: decimal
  +isActive: bool
}

class CouponRule {
  +startAt: datetime
  +endAt: datetime
  +maxUsage: int
}

class WishlistItem {
  +id: UUID
  +userId: UUID
  +productId: UUID
}

class Review {
  +id: UUID
  +userId: UUID
  +productId: UUID
  +rating: int
  +content: string
  +status: string
}

class ReviewReply {
  +id: UUID
  +reviewId: UUID
  +staffId: UUID
  +content: string
}

class SupportTicket {
  +id: UUID
  +userId: UUID
  +type: string
  +status: string
}

class ChatbotSession {
  +id: UUID
  +userId: UUID
  +contextJson: text
}

class ReportSummary {
  +totalUsers: int
  +totalProducts: int
  +totalOrders: int
  +totalRevenue: decimal
}

class AuthService
class ProductService
class CartService
class OrderService
class PaymentService
class ReviewService
class CouponService
class SupportService
class ReportService

User "1" -- "1" Profile
User "1" -- "*" Address
Category "1" -- "*" Product
Product "1" -- "*" ProductVariant
ProductVariant "1" -- "*" InventoryLog
User "1" -- "1" Cart
Cart "1" -- "*" CartItem
User "1" -- "*" Order
Order "1" -- "*" OrderItem
Order "1" -- "1" Payment
Coupon "1" -- "1" CouponRule
User "1" -- "*" WishlistItem
User "1" -- "*" Review
Review "1" -- "*" ReviewReply
User "1" -- "*" SupportTicket
User "1" -- "*" ChatbotSession

AuthService ..> User
ProductService ..> Product
ProductService ..> Category
CartService ..> Cart
CartService ..> CartItem
OrderService ..> Order
OrderService ..> OrderItem
PaymentService ..> Payment
ReviewService ..> Review
CouponService ..> Coupon
SupportService ..> SupportTicket
ReportService ..> ReportSummary

@enduml //


================================================================
3) ERD (ENTITY RELATIONSHIP DIAGRAM)
================================================================

3.1 Textual description

User-management:
- users (PK: id)
- profiles (PK/FK: user_id -> users.id)
- addresses (PK: id, FK: user_id -> users.id)

Catalog:
- categories (PK: id)
- products (PK: id, FK: category_id -> categories.id)
- product_variants (PK: id, FK: product_id -> products.id)
- inventory_logs (PK: id, FK: variant_id -> product_variants.id)

Shopping:
- carts (PK: id, FK: user_id -> users.id)
- cart_items (PK: id, FK: cart_id -> carts.id, FK: variant_id -> product_variants.id)
- wishlists (PK: id, FK: user_id -> users.id, FK: product_id -> products.id)

Order-payment:
- orders (PK: id, FK: user_id -> users.id, FK: address_id -> addresses.id, FK: coupon_id -> coupons.id)
- order_items (PK: id, FK: order_id -> orders.id, FK: variant_id -> product_variants.id)
- payments (PK: id, FK: order_id -> orders.id)
- coupons (PK: id)

Review-support:
- reviews (PK: id, FK: user_id -> users.id, FK: product_id -> products.id)
- review_replies (PK: id, FK: review_id -> reviews.id, FK: staff_id -> users.id)
- support_tickets (PK: id, FK: user_id -> users.id, FK: order_id -> orders.id nullable)
- chatbot_sessions (PK: id, FK: user_id -> users.id)


3.2 PlantUML ERD code (paste into PlantUML renderer)

@startuml
hide circle
skinparam linetype ortho

entity "users" as users {
  *id : uuid <<PK>>
  --
  email : varchar
  password_hash : varchar
  role : varchar
  status : varchar
  created_at : timestamptz
}

entity "profiles" as profiles {
  *user_id : uuid <<PK, FK>>
  --
  full_name : varchar
  phone : varchar
  avatar_url : varchar
  updated_at : timestamptz
}

entity "addresses" as addresses {
  *id : uuid <<PK>>
  --
  user_id : uuid <<FK>>
  receiver_name : varchar
  phone : varchar
  address_line : text
  is_default : boolean
}

entity "categories" as categories {
  *id : uuid <<PK>>
  --
  name : varchar
  slug : varchar
}

entity "products" as products {
  *id : uuid <<PK>>
  --
  category_id : uuid <<FK>>
  name : varchar
  price : numeric
  status : varchar
}

entity "product_variants" as variants {
  *id : uuid <<PK>>
  --
  product_id : uuid <<FK>>
  color : varchar
  size : varchar
  stock_qty : int
}

entity "inventory_logs" as inv_logs {
  *id : uuid <<PK>>
  --
  variant_id : uuid <<FK>>
  change_qty : int
  reason : varchar
  created_at : timestamptz
}

entity "carts" as carts {
  *id : uuid <<PK>>
  --
  user_id : uuid <<FK>>
  created_at : timestamptz
}

entity "cart_items" as cart_items {
  *id : uuid <<PK>>
  --
  cart_id : uuid <<FK>>
  variant_id : uuid <<FK>>
  quantity : int
}

entity "coupons" as coupons {
  *id : uuid <<PK>>
  --
  code : varchar
  discount_type : varchar
  discount_value : numeric
  start_at : timestamptz
  end_at : timestamptz
  max_usage : int
  is_active : boolean
}

entity "orders" as orders {
  *id : uuid <<PK>>
  --
  user_id : uuid <<FK>>
  address_id : uuid <<FK>>
  coupon_id : uuid <<FK, nullable>>
  status : varchar
  total_amount : numeric
  created_at : timestamptz
}

entity "order_items" as order_items {
  *id : uuid <<PK>>
  --
  order_id : uuid <<FK>>
  variant_id : uuid <<FK>>
  quantity : int
  unit_price : numeric
}

entity "payments" as payments {
  *id : uuid <<PK>>
  --
  order_id : uuid <<FK>>
  method : varchar
  status : varchar
  paid_at : timestamptz
  transaction_ref : varchar
}

entity "wishlists" as wishlists {
  *id : uuid <<PK>>
  --
  user_id : uuid <<FK>>
  product_id : uuid <<FK>>
  created_at : timestamptz
}

entity "reviews" as reviews {
  *id : uuid <<PK>>
  --
  user_id : uuid <<FK>>
  product_id : uuid <<FK>>
  rating : int
  content : text
  status : varchar
  created_at : timestamptz
}

entity "review_replies" as review_replies {
  *id : uuid <<PK>>
  --
  review_id : uuid <<FK>>
  staff_id : uuid <<FK>>
  content : text
  created_at : timestamptz
}

entity "support_tickets" as tickets {
  *id : uuid <<PK>>
  --
  user_id : uuid <<FK>>
  order_id : uuid <<FK, nullable>>
  type : varchar
  subject : varchar
  content : text
  status : varchar
  created_at : timestamptz
}

entity "chatbot_sessions" as chatbot_sessions {
  *id : uuid <<PK>>
  --
  user_id : uuid <<FK>>
  context_json : text
  created_at : timestamptz
}

users ||--|| profiles
users ||--o{ addresses
categories ||--o{ products
products ||--o{ variants
variants ||--o{ inv_logs
users ||--|| carts
carts ||--o{ cart_items
variants ||--o{ cart_items
users ||--o{ orders
addresses ||--o{ orders
coupons ||--o{ orders
orders ||--o{ order_items
variants ||--o{ order_items
orders ||--|| payments
users ||--o{ wishlists
products ||--o{ wishlists
users ||--o{ reviews
products ||--o{ reviews
reviews ||--o{ review_replies
users ||--o{ review_replies
users ||--o{ tickets
orders ||--o{ tickets
users ||--o{ chatbot_sessions

@enduml


================================================================
4) HOW TO RENDER TO IMAGE
================================================================

Option A (PlantUML online):
1. Open [PlantUML Server](https://www.plantuml.com/plantuml/uml/).
2. Copy one code block at a time (Use Case / Class / ERD).
3. Export PNG/SVG and insert images back into report.

Option B (VS Code plugin PlantUML):
1. Save each code block into separate .puml files.
2. Preview and export diagrams directly.


================================================================
5) SCOPE NOTE
================================================================

This document follows BUSINESS SCOPE from provided requirement images (User/Staff/Admin),
not limited to currently implemented repository features.

